journal_entry: Breakfast with H D Ciombs dinner with Albert Joy wrote letter to CC Burrill came home went to Lodge of Good Templars
Breakfast at Wm. Joys dinner at Same Woods wrote letter to CC Burrill came home
In the Ins. wrote a letter to CC burrill one to Hale & Emery
Breakfast with Hannah G dinner wtih Dr. Johnson wrote letter to CC burrill supper and Lodging with Hannah Goodwin
reed letter from C.C. Burrill wrote letter to CC Burrill one to Dr Johnson
wrote letter to CC Burill
Wrote a letter to J Martin one to CC Burrill out wind finished mowing
Furrowed over head and studied of the sorms wrote letter to C C Burrill dinner as usual. went to Political lecture gone one hour and 15 min.
Loafing or trying to sell a piece of land wrote letter to Charles C. Burrill
Fair weather the wind West wrote a letter to C. C. Burrill. Geo. N. Loomis. Went on board Schr A. G. Brooks to see about putting a house on. Wrote letters to Geo. N. Loomis. C. C. Burrill
The wind Southerly worked one half day building Galley on A. G. Brooks wrote letter to Thomas Bunker, Recd one from Augustus Gerrish.
The wind southerly started in the Schr Banner for Calais got to Mark Island thick fog dinner on board went back home wrote letter Benj Kittridge East Eden
location: Winter Harbor, Mark Island, Winter Harbor

journal_entry: The wind South foggy went in Jones Cove got of two scow loads of wood wrote letter to Benj. Kittridge
The wind N.E. very cold and snowy went up the stream cutting wood wrote letter to Benj. Kittridge
The wind Southerly and warm wrote letter to Benj. Kittridge surveyed wood for Flora Gerrish worked in shop apart of the day on boat
The wind N.N.E. overcast hauled into the wharf in the morning wrote letter to Thos. Bunker
The wind W.N.W. hauled into the wharf to to fix the vessel. Wrote letter to Charles Burrill.
The wind N. W. very moderate and pleasant wrote letter home and one to Capt. Thomas Bunker
The wind South West and foggy made decoys for Geo Gerrish and dug potatoes wrote letter to Thomas Bunker.
The wind North and overcast. got under way in morning for home arrived at 9 am. got water and provision on board and got ready to go to Rockland wrote letter to Thomas Bunker
The wind Westerly moderate wrote letter to Benj. Kittridge work in shop
The wind westerly moderate wrote letters to Benj Kittridge and Aiken and Co Sent Signals bills to Aiken and Co. Ellsworth
notes: changed Kittredge to Kittridge, changed & to and, changed & to and, changes & to and

journal_entry: The wind very moderate South West and very warm snow melts fast.  wrote letter to Thomas Bunker recd one from Benj. Kittridge. work in shop
The wind South Easterly and rainy work in shop. Finished the Black Warior's wheel wrote letter to Benj. Kittridge.
notes: changed Warriors to Warrior's, changed Kittredge to Kittridge

journal_entry: Calm in morning wrote letter to Thomas Bunker work in the fore noon on the Harps cabbin In the afternoon the wind South East painted inside of dora in shop
The wind Easterly and misty. took the new dora out the shop and took her to the shore Wrote letter to Benj. Kittridge
The wind Westerly in forenoon work on Henriettas cabbin and gangway Southerly wind in afternoon wrote letter to C. C. Burrill
The wind Southerly work for J. M. Sargent on Schr Henrietta wrote letter to Benj. Kittidge.

The wind Southerly snow melts fast wrote lettters to Benj. Kittridge. Benj. Sowle and to the Penobscot fire Ins. Co. put dunnage on board of Schr Harp to go away rain in afternoon. Left Lodge of Good Templars
The wind North East rainy all day untill about sunset. the wind hauling to the North. wrote letters to Thomas Bunker Register of Probate Caroline Blaisdell and Saml. Libby
The wind North West wrote letter to Capt Thomas Bunker work in shop mending furniture met for rehearsal at G. W. Tracys store.
notes: wind direction entered in am as does not specify time of day

journal_entry: The wind South West wrote letter to Capt. Thomas Bunker
notes: wind direction entered in am as does not specify time of day

journal_entry: The wind Easterly and Rainy. wrote letters to Capt Thomas Bunker and J.T. Wallace Jr. Went to Prospect Harbor and took up note of $100. of H.D. Coombs
notes: wind direction entered in am as does not specify time of day, same with weather cond

journal_entry: The wind Northerly wrote letters to Stephen Southard Thomas Bunker & Mejsrs S Le Muney &Co. went to Ellsworth with L. G. Cranes horse after money got $500.
notes: unsure in bold, wind direction entered in am as does not specify time of day

journal_entry: The wind N.N.W. could not load recd letter from Perley and Russell wrote letters to Chas Eaton Greens Landing and Benj. Kittridge
The wind Easterly and snowed took dinner on board the A. G. Brooks. wrote letter to Mrs F. R. Bunker and Benj. Kittridge
notes: changed Kittredge to Kittridge, changed & to and

journal_entry: The wind North East very moderate all day with snow wrote letters to Hancock Co Pub Co and Thomas Bunker work in shop.
The wind Northerly wrote letters to Ellsworth American Benj. Kittridge and sent Papers of Amulets and Signal to Benj Kittridge also a statement of the Amulets account for the year ending 1874
work in shop reed a letter from CC Burrill Ellsworth one from George N Loomis
Read letter from CC Burrill went to West Gouldsboro in the Ins. Busi took tea with Edward Kingsley Lodging with Samuel Wood
Went to Turtle Isle. Eve went to Lodge recd letter from CC Burrill & Hale & Emery
location: Winter Harbor, Turtle Isle, Winter Harbor

journal_entry: reed letter from C.C. Burrill wrote letter to CC Burrill one to Dr Johnson
painted boat took dinner at J Smallidges reed letter from CC Burrill went to Lodge
local_place: Josiah Smallidge's, Lodge of Good Templars

journal_entry: Stormy work in shop reed letter from CC Burrill also oil painting of Niagara Falls by moon light went to Lodge of G. Templar lodgign at Thos. Smallidge
local_place: Shop, Lodge of Good Templars, Thomas Smallidge's
notes: This oil painting of Niagara Falls by moon light actually exists, so cool! by Hermann Herzog. Little random in text though..

journal_entry: Getting out window Jams reed letter from C. C. Burrill. dinner at usual place while to work on house
Reed letter from Chas. C. Burrill
Hauling home brick shingles and boards from S Guptills wharf went to Lodge. Reed letter from CC Burrill
local_place: Home, S. Guptill's Wharf, Lodge of Good Templars

journal_entry: The wind very moderate or calm work in shop on boat. Recd letter from Thomas Bunker Cranberry Isles
The wind West and warm Recd letter from C. C. Burrill done turning for R. Rand filed saw for Chas Norris got out gunnels for boat went to Lodge of G. T. paid C. Steven $60 for G. W. Tracy
local_place: Home, Shop, G. T. 's Lodge, Home

journal_entry: The wind Eastward went on Iron Bound to work for Galen Smith dinner and supper at his house came home rain and blowed heavy in Evening recd letter from Thomas Bunker
location: Winter Harbor, Iron Bound, Winter Harbor

journal_entry: The wind Northerly passed Petitmanan at 6 got home at 9 AM in the afternoon made a pair steps for the Amarild recd letter from Benj. Kittridge
The wind S.W. foggy got underway at 2 PM. sunset on Bass Harbor bar the wind N.W. arrived at Home at 11 P.M. recd letters from Thos. Bunker. Benj. Kittridge A. D. Crabtree
location: Deer Isle, Bass Harbor, Winter Harbor

journal_entry: The wind NE in the morning went around to the Southard got home at noon and landed freight recd letter from Benj. Kittridge G. L. Hodgkins
The wind N.W. got under way and went to Bass Harbor until the wind moderated arrived at home at dark recd letter from Thomas Bunker and Nathan Goodwin
location: Deer Isle, Bass Harbor, Winter Harbor

journal_entry: The wind very moderate in forenoon fresh breeze in afternoon could not go to loading and walked home. Recd letter from Benj. Kittridge
notes: changed Kittredge to Kittridge, Georgia Foss baby died AM. was crossed out

journal_entry: Calm and foggy went gunning and got 5 coots back home at noon. Recd letters from Benj. Kittridge and A. N. Willey gathered garden.
The wind West S.West got underway at day light and got home at one oclock and set up with Stillman Smallidge all night recd letters from Thomas Bunker Hale and Emery Continal life Ins Co.
The wind N.W. in fore noon calm in afternoon came out of the woods recd letter from Benj. Kittridge went to Lodge of Good Templars
local_place: Woods, Home, Lodge of Good Templars, Home

journal_entry: The wind N.W. very cold came out of the woods recd Reg. letters from Thomas Bunker
The wind southerly and rainy recd letters from Benj. Kittridge Dr. Lewis work in shop.
The wind Southerly work on vessel painting scaping etc. recd letter from Charly Burrill.
The wind Northerly hauled into the wharf recd letter from Thomas Bunker
The wind Northerly and cold cut wood all day came out at night recd letter from Benj. Kitttridge
The wind North West work in shop recd letter from Benj. Kittridge wrote letter to W. B. McCrate.
The wind Westerly good breeze finished saw table recd letter from Benj. Kittridge
The wind very moderate South West and very warm snow melts fast.  wrote letter to Thomas Bunker recd one from Benj. Kittridge. work in shop
The wind North East snow in fore noon and clear in afternoon work in shop on dora recd letter from Capt Thomas Bunker and Caroline Blaisdell.
The wind W. N. W. very heavy blow run wind mill turning belaying pins etc. Recd letter from Capt Thomas Bunker
The wind N. N. East wrote letters to Secreraty of Treasury in the afternoon the wind out Southerly worked on the Harp recd letter from Benj. Kittridge

The wind Southerly. and foggy in fore noon sun out in afternoon snow melt very fast. made upper pump box for Schr Lebanon work for J. M. Sargent in afternoon and finished work for him on vessel recd letter from Benj. Kittridge
The wind North good breeze my wages commenced on board Schr Harp With Capt Nathan Bickford loosed sails. to dry etc. Recd letters from Benj. Kittridge and Penobscot Mutual Fire Ins Co
notes: changed &c to etc., changed Kittredge to Kittridge

journal_entry: The wind South West Work all day in Hall building stage. Reed letter from Thomas Bunker
notes: wind direction entered in am as does not specify time of day

journal_entry: The wind Southerly put pipe in hugs heads for water wrote letter to Lynam Toby Sleo Portland Reed letter from Capt Thomas Bunker
notes: unsure in bold,  wind direction entered in am as does not specify time of day

journal_entry: The wind N.N.West. wrote letter to J. A Milliken Cherryfield. Work hauling stone around the house. reed letters from Thomas Bunker Cranberry Isles. And C C Burril at Ellsworth.
notes: wind direction entered in am as does not specify time of day

journal_entry: Breakfast wtih Hannah G dinner with Stephen Kingsly reed letter from Hale Emery one from CC burrill came home
The wind very moderate to the N.W put gunnels on boat and risings recd letter from Geo. W. Butler, C. C. Burrill
The wind S.W. foggy got underway at 2 PM. sunset on Bass Harbor bar the wind N.W. arrived at Home at 11 P.M. recd letters from Thos. Bunker. Benj. Kittridge A. D. Crabtree
location: Deer Isle, Bass Harbor, Winter Harbor

journal_entry: The wind N.N.W. commenced discharging in evening. wrote letter to my wife and recd one from her also from B. Kittridge and Mrs. L. Hammond
The wind N. East went fishing raining read letters from Geo. A. Dyer. Arno Wiswell. Charles C. Burrill all of Ellsworth also one from Perley and Russell of Portland.
notes: also written Burrel in transcript, but probably C. C. Burrill
